rComments: Like most professors, Harrison is primarily engaged in research with teaching as a required job. This shows in his teaching abilities, which is pretty much directly from the PowerPoint slides.

Professor Harrison does not teach what is on the exams or the homeworks. He mainly teaches what he finds interesting. For instance, while we were talking about datapaths today, he referenced EAX registers in his lecture. It depends on if you like the excess material or not. Most of what you learn comes from the lecture slides.
The subject itself is very interesting but the professor makes it dull and boring. He reads off the Power Point slides and that does not help students to learn the material effectively.
